rComments: On the plus side, Prof Hecht seems to like teaching a lot, and frequently offers to teach students non-examinable material outside of class, if they're interested. On the other hand, he puts very little effort into actually teaching. His lectures are convoluted, and he puts the bare minimum effort into structuring the class and writing his exams.

Great professor. Had Tort Law in 1L with him. I would recommend him to any incoming 1L students. Exams are very fair, although he did not do a great job in explaining his assignments which caused some confusion. Overall, great prof.

Professor Hecht was my favourite prof in first year. Definitely a prof who cares a lot about his students and wants to see you succeed. Interesting coverage of the material while keeping students involved. Exams and assignments are very fair. Would 10/10 recommend taking a course from him.
Nice person, tries to cover material in interesting manner and fair exam.

Outstanding guy.  Good prof.  Tough to follow in French - his French is not up to par to teaching a course in French.  But, he gave us every opportunity to improve, ask questions, do papers - and his review was top notch!
Very tough to follow Torts in French.  But he was super kind in going over and over again our queries and his course review was EXCELLENT!
